JOHANNESBURG - Television personality Palesa Madisakwane was in the firing line on twitter on Friday, after she criticised musician and actor Zola 7. Madisakwane, who is also employed as a news anchor at ANN7, called Zola “irrelevant” and told him to “stop acting like a celebrity”, after Zola refused to grant the channel an interview during Joe Mafela’s memorial service on Thursday. On behalf of my assistant n myself. My sincere apologies @Zola7Real n south africa. I knew bout tweet but didn't think she'd use such words Bonginkosi "Zola" Dlamini speaks about #JoeMafela. #JoeMafelaMemorial pic.twitter.com/KOpeOsGWGF Some Twitter users defended the musician, saying it was his right to decide if he wanted to be interviewed or not. Madisakwane deleted her tweets and later wrote that her PR/Assistant posted on her behalf. She then issued an apology to Zola and South Africans who were offended by her posts. we will forever be loyal to Zola , just like Zola has been loyal to the black child !! #zola #Palesa and irrelevance.#Zola is a living legend,I love that man. pic.twitter.com/mGIqm3olMt When #Palesa calls Zola irrelevant but no one knows who she is pic.twitter.com/cHHiCHPUua If you missed the #Palesa attack on #Zola
		
